data.text:
Jeffry Lane "Jeff" Flake (born 31 December 1962) was a US Senator from Arizona (R) from 3 January 2013 to 3 January 2019, succeeding Jon Kyl and preceding Kyrsten Sinema. He previously served in the US House of Representatives (R-AZ 1) from 3 January 2001 to 3 January 2003 (succeeding Matt Salmon and preceding Rick Renzi) and from 3 January 2003 to 3 January 2013 (succeeding J.D. Hayworth and preceding David Schweikert).
